		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Detective fiction</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For the 1951 film, see <a href="/wiki/Detective_Story" title="Detective Story">Detective Story</a>.</div>
<p><b>Detective fiction</b> is a branch of <a href="/wiki/Crime_fiction" title="Crime fiction">crime fiction</a> in which a <a href="/wiki/Detective" title="Detective">detective</a> (or detectives), either professional or amateur, investigate a crime, usually <a href="/wiki/Murder" title="Murder">murder</a>. Detective fiction is the most popular form of both <a href="/wiki/Mystery_fiction" title="Mystery fiction" class="mw-redirect">mystery fiction</a> and <a href="/wiki/Hardboiled" title="Hardboiled">hardboiled</a> crime fiction.</p>
<p>Commonly in detective fiction, the investigator has some source of income other than detective work and some undesirable eccentricities or striking characteristics.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since January 2009" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> He or she frequently has a less able assistant (or <a href="/wiki/Foil_(literature)" title="Foil (literature)">foil</a>) who acts as an <a href="/wiki/Audience_surrogate" title="Audience surrogate">audience surrogate</a> for the explanation of the mystery at the end of the story.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since January 2009" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
